---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy - Pikos" description="Pikos privacy policy. Your data stays on your device. Plain language, no legalese.">

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-8 py-20">

    <!-- Back to home -->
    <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-gray-400 transition-colors hover:text-orange-500 dark:text-gray-500 dark:hover:text-orange-400">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m15 18-6-6 6-6"/></svg>
      Home
    </a>

    <h1 class="mt-8 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">Last updated: March 29, 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">

      <p>
        Pikos is a local-first app. This policy is short because we don't collect much. Here's exactly what happens with your data.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">What stays on your device</h2>

      <p>
        Everything you create in Pikos — notes, tasks, calendar events, folders, and settings — is stored in a local SQLite database on your machine. This data never leaves your device unless you explicitly choose to sync it.
      </p>

      <p>
        We cannot access, read, or recover your data. There is no server-side copy. If you delete the app, the data goes with it (unless you've backed it up yourself).
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">What leaves your device (only with your action)</h2>

      <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>iCloud sync:</strong> If you enable sync, your data is transferred via Apple's iCloud infrastructure using your Apple account. Pikos does not operate any sync servers. Apple's iCloud privacy policy governs that data in transit and at rest on their servers.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Email address (waitlist only):</strong> If you signed up on this website for early access, we stored your email address to send you one launch notification. We use <a href="https://resend.com" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">Resend</a> to send that email. We don't sell, share, or use your email for anything else.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">What we never collect</h2>

      <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-2">
        <li>Note content, task titles, or calendar event details</li>
        <li>Usage analytics or telemetry from the desktop app</li>
        <li>Cookies, fingerprints, or tracking pixels</li>
        <li>Personal information beyond what you voluntarily provide</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">Website analytics</h2>

      <p>
        This website (pikos.app) may use privacy-first analytics to count page views. No cookies, no personal data, no cross-site tracking. You are never individually identified.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">Data export</h2>

      <p>
        Your data is stored in a standard SQLite database file on your device. You can copy, back up, or inspect it at any time using any SQLite-compatible tool. There is no lock-in.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">Changes to this policy</h2>

      <p>
        If this policy changes, we'll update the date at the top. For material changes (like collecting new data), we'll note it clearly here and, if possible, notify you in the app.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">Contact</h2>

      <p>
        Questions about privacy? Email <a href="mailto:hello@pikos.app" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">hello@pikos.app</a>.
      </p>

    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="mt-20 border-t border-gray-100 pt-8 dark:border-gray-800">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-sm text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">
        <a href="/" class="transition-colors hover:text-orange-500 dark:hover:text-orange-400">Home</a>
        <a href="/about" class="transition-colors hover:text-orange-500 dark:hover:text-orange-400">About</a>
        <span>Pikos by <a href="https://alexking.dev" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">Alex</a></span>
      </div>
    </footer>

  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  :global(body) {
    background-color: #fafaf9;
  }

  :global(html.dark body) {
    background-color: #030712;
  }
</style>
